<p><strong>Damage Resistances</strong> bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical weapons</p>

<p><strong>Damage Immunities</strong> fire</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Ignan</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 1/2 (100 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Death Burst.</em></strong> When the magmin dies, it explodes in a burst of fire and magma. Each creature within 10 ft. of it must make a DC 11 Dexterity saving throw, taking 7 (2d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Flammable objects that arenâ€™t being worn or carried in that area are ignited.</p>

<p><strong><em>Ignited Illumination.</em></strong> As a bonus action, the magmin can set itself ablaze or extinguish its flames. While ablaze, the magmin sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Touch.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 7 (2d6) fire damage. If the target is a creature or a flammable object, it ignites. Until a creature takes an action to douse the fire, the creature takes 3 (1d6) fire damage at the end of each of its turns.</p>

